sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates a target group.

Inputs:

  • Region - Amazon region.
  • Target Group ARN - ARN of target group.
  • Port - Port on which the targets receive traffic.
  • Protocol - Protocol used for routing traffic to the targets.
  • VPC ID - Identifier of the virtual private cloud (VPC).

Outputs:

  • Target Group ARN
  • Health Check Enabled
  • Health Check Interval Seconds
  • Health Check Timeout Seconds

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

  • Error Messages:
    • Target groups ARN not found.
    (For information about the errors that are common to all actions, see Common Errors).

    To use this action, the corresponding AWS Elastic Load Balancing connection and credential must be created and associated with the AWS Elastic Load Balancing Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

sys_hub_action_type_snapshot.description:
Creates a target group.

Inputs:

  • Region - Amazon region.
  • Target Group ARN - ARN of target group.
  • Port - Port on which the targets receive traffic.
  • Protocol - Protocol used for routing traffic to the targets.
  • VPC ID - Identifier of the virtual private cloud (VPC).

Outputs:

  • Target Group ARN
  • Health Check Enabled
  • Health Check Interval Seconds
  • Health Check Timeout Seconds

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

  • Error Messages:
    • Target groups ARN not found.
    (For information about the errors that are common to all actions, see Common Errors).

    To use this action, the corresponding AWS Elastic Load Balancing connection and credential must be created and associated with the AWS Elastic Load Balancing Connection & Credential alias. Learn More
